===message:I am not sure what you mean by phrased.  However, you posed a good question.  Hitler was bent on expansion.  What I meant by my statement was that if Hitler would have been confronted immediately and not passified, then the war in Europe would have been kept on a smaller scale.  As you pointed out, the Sudentland gave Hitler an advantage.  This advantage came not only from its positioning, but also from the idea that if confronted, Britain and the other European countries would bend to whatever wills Hitler had.  By no means am I predicting that the war would not have happened if Hitler would not have been pacified, but I do think that the war could have been put on a smaller scale, thus restricting the scale of the war.  I hope that answers your question.  Please, tell me what you meant by "phrased" and what you think of my answer.  Thank you for your reply and the quality of your reply.  
