===subject:good points
===from:Chris Schmidt
===date:Fri Mar 21 21:53:13 2003
===message:<p>These are great points and shed an incredible amount of light on the US's role in today's world. The US dominance in post WWII Europe allowed Western Europe to focus on issues other than military developement. The US was there to prevent the spread of Communist aggression, and the Europeans formed the first real European peace in history. I think it would be interesting to see what a turn-of-the-century Frenchman or Englishman would have thought of a European Union. It would have been a joke. I think that war is avoidable by a nation only if it is sheltered by another. A weak nation is doomed to be on the recieving end of power politics and a strong nation will be drawn into conflict by a competing power. Today the US has asserted a unipolar influence on the world and our allies enjoy peace and disdain military force because of our protection.</p>
<p>Isolationism is very appealing. If the US pulled back it's massive global forces it would just open the door for another power to make a grab for dominance. While we could possibly remove ourselves from constant police actions and war, we would either end up alligned against a powerfull adversary or submitting to another nation for protection.</p>
=========yorg=========
